    "details": {
      "biography": {
        "value": "<p><em>A striking woman in her mid-thirties with rich auburn hair in a partially-pinned style, sharp green eyes behind a warm public smile, and the confident bearing of someone who has never needed to raise her voice. She dresses fashionably without severity — warm rather than austere — which is deliberate.</em></p><h3>Personality</h3><p>Warmly charming, receptive, and strategically patient. She appears interested rather than ambitious. She listens more than she speaks with new acquaintances and remembers everything.</p><h3>Motivation</h3><p>To construct a commercial and political position so structurally embedded in the city's economy that her influence becomes a fact of civic life rather than a personality contest.</p><h3>Mannerisms</h3><p>Listens completely before responding; asks follow-up questions slightly more specific than comfortable; volunteers small personal admissions that create false intimacy; never checks whether she is the most powerful person in a room — she already knows.</p><h3>Voice &amp; Accent</h3><p>Warm, measured, attentive. She speaks as if the person she is talking to is the most relevant person she has encountered this week.</p><h3>Bonds, Ideals, Flaws</h3><ul><li><strong>Bond:</strong> She is genuinely fond of her younger brother Daven, who knows nothing of her methods.</li><li><strong>Ideal:</strong> Patience is power. The person who waits the longest in the right position wins every negotiation.</li><li><strong>Flaw:</strong> She has underestimated Elira Storme's depth of resource.</li></ul><hr><h3>GM Notes</h3><p>Use Orvaine as a second political layer beneath Elira — younger, warmer in presentation, and building something Elira has not yet noticed. Can be ally, information source on Elira's methods, or long-term rival. Connects to Edra Fosse trade license plot and Cael financial arrangement.</p><h3>Secrets</h3><p>Her commercial network will give her leverage over significant city import commerce within two years. She shares a financial arrangement with Cael neither has named. She knows more about Elira's orphan fund mechanism than Elira realizes.</p><h3>Relationships</h3><p>Lady Elira Storme: political rival whom Orvaine does not underestimate while Elira underestimates her. | Cael: silent financial overlap neither has named. | Quilby Thistledown: she finds him charming; he finds her dangerous. | Edra Fosse: has begun noticing patterns Orvaine prefers unnoticed.</p><h3>Plot Hooks</h3><p>1. Orvaine requests a favor framed as personal — it also damages one of Elira's interests.\n2. Edra Fosse's documentation traces to silent partnerships in Orvaine's name.\n3. The party discovers the Cael-Orvaine connection before either knows.\n4. Orvaine quietly acquires something the party was cultivating before they noticed she was watching.</p><h3>Encounter Ideas</h3><p>1. Council reception where Orvaine speaks privately with each party member before Elira has greeted them.\n2. Orvaine requests a discreet meeting and arrives exactly on time with no visible preparation.\n3. A party member receives a perfectly chosen gift from Orvaine without knowing what it signals.</p>",
